cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.GT

This paper deals with a problem of user association in a small cell network, which is a subfield of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of energy harvesting and consumption, which falls under information theory (cs.IT). The probabilistic framework and bandit-theoretical formulation used in the paper are related to control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA). Finally, the analysis of QoS satisfaction and user association can be considered as a game-theoretical problem (cs.GT).
